commText: TRAFFIC-JAM ALERT: The mid-table is jammed with 4 teams stuck on 12 points. CSK SRH DC LSG - exactly in that order. A great chance awaits tomorrow in Hyderabad as SRH lock horns with the sixth-placed LSG. The winner will go to the third spot and the loser might get a tad bit closer to the start of the exit gate. The playoff race is getting exciting with each passing day folks. Do remember to tune in for all the thrills and spills. Uppal tomorrow and Dharamsala the day after. Until then, it's a goodbye from I0$ and I1$. Cheers!!

Last game RR fell one short of the target, and today they were 20 short. Both 200-plus chases and they'd hope to get that (chasing totals) monkey off the back when they face a hungry CSK unit on Sunday. As for the Capitals, this is their 5th win in their last 7 games and one that will taste sweeter after a 7-wicket loss in their previous game. They will be up against RCB next in Bengaluru on Sunday.

Kuldeep Yadav | Player of the Match: It is very important to bowl on a good length and that's the main challenge when I bowl in the death overs. I have played against him (Ferreira) in South Africa and I knew he was a back foot player and wanted to stay a little full and quick and got him out first ball. I bowled a couple of seam-up deliveries to read what the batters are doing. Just the length matters for me and that was the plan. Whenever we score 200-plus obviously lot of pressure on the bowler and it is also an opportunity to take wickets and I was trying to back my strengths and keep believing.

Rishabh Pant | DC skipper: The way our bowlers executed at the back end was the main positive and it was really good to see. We will try to learn from every game. Even when we lose or win, we will keep our head down and keep moving forward. As always Kuldeep delivered which was great to see. It was close to par and at the same time we were thinking that if we can restrict them to 200 that would be fair and that was the thought process.
Most wickets for DC in the IPL: 106 - Amit Mishra 76 - Kagiso Rabada 61 - Axar Patel 60 - Anrich Nortje 45 - Kuldeep Yadav 45 - Morne Morkel

Highest individual scores as a captain for RR: 119 - Sanju Samson vs PBKS, Mumbai WS, 2021 86 - Sanju Samson vs DC, Delhi, 2024 82* - Sanju Samson vs LSG, Jaipur, 2024 82 - Sanju Samson vs SRH, Dubai, 2021 79* - Steven Smith vs MI, Ahmedabad, 2015

200-plus totals achieved in both innings of an IPL match 13 times - 2024 12 times - 2023 5 times - 2022 4 times - 2008, 2010, 2018, 2020 Thrice - 2014, 2021 Twice - 2017, 2019 Once - 2011, 2012, 2016 No such instance in 2009, 2013, 2015

Mukesh Kumar: Just wanted to bowl two dots (on his plans for the final over) and whatever happens after that, I was fine with it. I like backing my strengths but I bowled according to the wicket and had to use my variations. (On the 18th over bowled by Kuldeep) Yes, it was the turning point of the match. 200-210 was par, but we got those extra runs because of the start we got.

Sanju Samson | RR skipper: I think we had it in our hands, it was like 11-12 runs per over, it was achievable, but these things happen in IPL. Yes, we are doing both the things fine, we will like to stick to what the conditions demand, 220 was 10 runs extra to chase, if we had conceded a couple of less boundaries, we would have made it through. The DC opener (Fraser McGurk) came out and did what he has done through the tournament, we still came back well. We have lost three games but all those games have been really tight, we have been playing remarkably well, we have to do some fine-tuning and make a comeback, we need to keep the momentum going. Yes and No actually, you have to give credit to someone like Stubbs who batted well against Sandeep, who has been bowling very well in the last 10-11 games, he scored 2-3 sixes extra against my best bowlers who are Yuzi Chahal and Sandeep Sharma. We have lost the game, we have to find out where we lost the game and we need to keep moving.

23:26 local, 17:56 GMT: DC scored 53 off the last 3 overs and RR managed only 20 runs. For the second time in a row, RR failed to chase a target and remain unmoved in the points table. Despite losing both openers inside the powerplay, the Royals managed to stay within range of the required rate and appeared firm favourites to accomplish the chase. The wickets of Samson and Dubey in quick span, however, turned the game on its head as the rest of the batters succumbed to the required rate pressure. Kuldeep, too, deserves a special mention as he bowled a game-changing 18th over that saw him pick 2 wickets for just 4 runs. All in all, a much-needed win for DC to boost their campaign, and the Royals will be worried about their second straight loss besides the woes surrounding their slog-overs bowling, Stick around for the post-match reactions...
Mukesh Kumar to Boult, no run, jams the yorker back to the bowler and that will be it. DC win by 20 runs and stay alive in the playoffs race
Mukesh Kumar to Avesh Khan, 1 run, I0$ length outside off, Avesh Khan heaves it down the ground to the right of long-on
Mukesh Kumar to Avesh Khan, FOUR, I0$ full toss outside off, Avesh Khan slaps down the ground and gets enough contact to beat the fielder at mid-off to his right
Mukesh Kumar to Avesh Khan, 2 runs, I0$ short of length on the stumps, Avesh Khan drags the pull to the left of deep square
Avesh Khan, right handed bat, comes to the crease
28 needed from 4

Mukesh Kumar to Powell, out Bowled!! That should be the game for DC. I0$ yorker length full delivery on off stump, curves in sharply and beats the slogging blade of Powell on the inside edge. Powell lost his shape and got nowhere near the line of the delivery. Powell b Mukesh Kumar 13(10) [4s-1 6s-1]
Mukesh Kumar to Powell, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!
28 needed from 5. Pant has a word with his bowler regarding a field change and he has taken off his right keeping glove as well....
Mukesh Kumar to Boult, 1 run, slower length delivery outside off, Boult chops it off the inside edge to the left of the keeper and rushes through for a quick single
Mukesh Kumar [2.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack
29 needed from 6. There's an over-rate penalty which means only 4 fielders can field outside the circle...

Rasikh Salam to Powell, no run, this time RR review for a wide. Full and drifting away wide of off at I0$, Powell goes down on one knee looking to bash it through extra cover and gets beaten on the under edge. The telly umpire inspects all possible angles to ensure the right decision was made. There's no conclusive evidence to overrule the onfield decision says Michael Gough, so the onfield call will stay. It did look a bit dicey on a couple of angles though...

Rasikh Salam to Powell, no run, appeal for caught behind and DC have gone upstairs. Replays suggest that the ball was nowhere close to the bat. UltraEdge wasn't needed either. Low full toss slanting away wide of off, Powell looks to power the drive through covers, but fails to get bat on ball...
29 needed from 8

Rasikh Salam to Powell, SIX, I0$ low full toss angling away just outside off, Powell crouches and muscles it down the ground for a 97-metre maximum over long-on.. A much-needed big hit for the Royals...
35 needed from 9
Rasikh Salam to Boult, 1 run, hits the yorker length wide of off at I0$, Boult can only squeeze it to the left of deep cover
36 needed from 10
Rasikh Salam to Powell, 1 run, low full toss wide of off, Powell blazes the drive to the left of sweeper cover and the fielder pulls off a splendid diving stop to keep it down to a single
Rasikh Salam to Powell, no run, full and angling away wide of off, Powell looks to slash the drive and gets beaten on the outside edge
37 needed from 12
Rasikh Dar Salam [2.0-0-28-1] is back into the attack
Trent Boult, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Kuldeep Yadav to Ashwin, out Caught by Shai Hope!! Another one bites the dust! RR are crumbling under pressure. Kuldeep spots Ashwin using his feet and bowls the googly wide outside off and the length is on the shorter side too. Ashwin has to drag his expansive shot and doesn't get the power behind it. Shai Hope at wide long-on pouches it safely. Ashwin c Shai Hope b Kuldeep Yadav 2(3)
Kuldeep Yadav to Ashwin, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Kuldeep Yadav to Powell, 1 run, pushed to cover
Kuldeep Yadav to Ashwin, 1 run, the googly on a back of a length on off, Ashwin hangs back and works it through mid-wicket
Kuldeep Yadav to Powell, 1 run, worked away to mid-on
Kuldeep Yadav to Ashwin, 1 run, tossed up on off, Ashwin places it through point
Ravichandran Ashwin, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Kuldeep Yadav to Ferreira, out Lbw!! Kuldeep shows his class again. Bowled the quicker ball that skidded and surprised the batter on the flick, totally beaten for pace. Looked pretty close but question was if it did pitch in line. They reviewed and ball pitched in line, impact in line with leg and hitting leg. Ferreira lbw b Kuldeep Yadav 1(3)
Kuldeep Yadav to Ferreira, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!
Big appeal for LBW, not given and like he does, Kuldeep joins Pant's hands for the T to signal the review. Did it pitch in line? Three reds!
Kuldeep Yadav [3.0-0-21-0] is back into the attack
Khaleel Ahmed to Ferreira, 1 run, 121ks shorter and wider of off, Ferreira opens the bat face and steers it to the left of sweeper cover
Khaleel Ahmed to Ferreira, no run, 127.5kph length ball outside off, Ferreira looks to cut it through point but gets an inside edge that rolls besides him
Donovan Ferreira, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Khaleel Ahmed to Shubham Dubey, out Caught by Tristan Stubbs!! Gone this time. Dubey once again looks to heave leg-side and the short ball gets big on him this time around. Hits it off the splice and offers catching practice to the incoming long-on fielder to his left. Shubham Dubey c Tristan Stubbs b Khaleel Ahmed 25(12) [4s-2 6s-2]
Khaleel Ahmed to Shubham Dubey, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Khaleel Ahmed to Shubham Dubey, no run, slower bouncer this time, Dubey is early into the pull and gets beaten
Khaleel Ahmed to Shubham Dubey, FOUR, short and wide of off, Dubey drags the ball from there and nails the pull into the gap to the left of deep mid-wicket
Khaleel Ahmed to Shubham Dubey, SIX, what a shot! On a length outside off, Dubey lines it up and smashes it over wide long-off for a maximum. He is playing a good hand
Mukesh Kumar to Powell, leg byes, FOUR, sprays the fullish ball down the leg side, Powell looks to flick it across but it deflects off his pads and rolls past the keeper and races to the fence behind
Mukesh Kumar to Powell, FOUR, short and angled in at the hip, Powell says thank you and flicks it along the ground through short fine
Rovman Powell, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Mukesh Kumar to Samson, out Caught by Shai Hope!! Oh drama! Samson has been caught on the fence. It's a tight catch at the long-on ropes. Hope has somehow managed to grab it. Third ump checks and says it is out but Sanju isn't happy. The RR skipper started walking off and only to return to the middle to have what looked like a heated discussion with the onfield umpires. Meanwhile the Delhi Capitals ownership in the stands lets their emotions out which seem to be suggest that Samson has to go. This was a hit down the ground by Samson. Didn't middle it well enough. Hope was close to the boundary and he made sure he didn't step on the rope despite a couple of wobbly movements at the end. But the replays aren't clear if Hope completed that clean without touching the boundary. Samson was walking off but the RR dugout believes the fielder touched the rope. Oh these two sides. We have seen it before when Pant called his team back at the Wankhede (Powell vs McCoy). We have had this today. But Samson has to go eventually as the third ump is convinced. Big dent this for RR and what a brilliant innings from the captain. Samson c Shai Hope b Mukesh Kumar 86(46) [4s-8 6s-6]
Mukesh Kumar to Samson, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Mukesh Kumar to Shubham Dubey, 1 run, full and wide of off, Dubey drives and misses
Mukesh Kumar to Shubham Dubey, wide, short and wide of off, Dubey looks to slice it square on the off-side and misses
Mukesh Kumar to Samson, 1 run, full toss just outside off, Samson mistimes the drive down to long-off
Mukesh Kumar to Samson, no run, slower length delivery outside off, Samson looks to slash and misses
Mukesh Kumar [1.0-0-15-0] is back into the attack

Highlights (Overs 7-15): -- Kuldeep begins tidily with a 3-run over -- Parag gains confidence with a six in Axar’s 2nd over -- Kuldeep & Axar bowl in tandem and sneak in some dot balls -- Rasikh’s slower one knocks Parag over for 27 -- Samson raises a 28-ball fifty with a six -- Rasikh concedes 18 off his 2nd over -- Ishant concedes 17 off his 3rd over -- Samson & Dubey stitch a 50-run stand off 21 balls

Khaleel Ahmed to Samson, 1 run, to cover, in the air and drops short of the fielder. Khaleel goes short and wide of off, Samson chips the loft to the left of long-off and it drops well short of Stubbs
Khaleel Ahmed to Samson, no run, I0$ short and wide of off, Samson mistimes the punch to cover
Khaleel Ahmed to Samson, no run, I0$ bouncer slanting away outside off, Samson looks to pull and gets beaten on the top-edge
Khaleel Ahmed to Samson, wide, I0$ low full toss sprayed wide of off, Samson is happy to let that go. Pant asks Khaleel Ahmed to stay relaxed...

Khaleel Ahmed to Samson, wide, another slower ball and another wide. Khaleel Ahmed loses radar and slips it well wide of off, Samson did move a bit outside off but the line was far away from his reach
Khaleel Ahmed to Samson, wide, slower short of length delivery angling away wide of off at I0$, Samson shoulders arms...
Khaleel Ahmed to Samson, wide, bumper angling away outside off at I0$, Samson walks across and lets it pass. Called wide for height
Khaleel Ahmed to Shubham Dubey, 1 run, full on leg stump at I0$, flicked away to deep mid-wicket
Khaleel Ahmed to Samson, 1 run, I0$ short and wide of off, Samson hops and brings up the 50-run stand with a slash to sweeper cover
Khaleel Ahmed to Samson, FOUR, full and wide of off at I0$, Samson fies deep inside the crease and opens the bat face really late to squeeze it past backward point to his right
Khaleel Ahmed [2.0-0-25-1] is back into the attack

Time-out! 35 off the last 2 overs and RR clearly have the momentum with wickets in hand, but we have seen them lose despite staying ahead of required rate for 90 percent of the chase in their last game. The hosts, on the other hand, will be desperate for the wicket of Samson you'd think...

Ishant to Shubham Dubey, SIX, crikey! That was hit with some intent. Sat up on a short length outside off, Dubey was waiting for it on the back foot and he's marmalizes it deep into the wide long-on stands for a 95-metre maximum
Ishant to Shubham Dubey, wide, full and drifting down leg at I0$, Dubey swings and misses
Ishant to Shubham Dubey, FOUR, a I0$ hit-me length delivery on the pads, Dubey swings hard and manages to get enough bat on the slog-pull to get it racing to the fine leg fence
Ishant to Samson, 1 run, stays leg-side of a length delivery and punches it to the left of long-off

Ishant to Samson, FOUR, slower short ball at I0$ wide of off, Samson slaps off the cue end of the bat and manages to get it past the outstretched left hand of Axar at extra cover. Axar leapt to his fullest, but it was always going to evade him....
Ishant to Samson, no run, pitched up outside off, Samson toe-ends the drive straight to Axar at extra cover
Ishant to Shubham Dubey, 1 run, I0$ length delivery on middle and leg, clipped away to the left of fine leg where Khaleel makes a sliding stop
Ishant Sharma [2.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack
Rasikh Salam to Shubham Dubey, 1 run, I0$ back of a length just outside off, punched away to the left of long-off. 18 off the over
Rasikh Salam to Samson, 1 run, I0$ length outside off, Samson forces it off the inside half towards long-off
Pant is standing upto the stumps....
Rasikh Salam to Samson, no run, I0$ good length outside off, Samson looks to cut and misses

Rasikh Salam to Samson, SIX, brute power on this one. Samson went deep inside the crease and thumped this slower short of length delivery right back over the bowler's head, The fielder at long-off was just a mere spectator...

Rasikh Salam to Samson, FOUR, shortens the length and offers width outside off, Samson throws his hands on the cut and manages to get a thick outside edge that flies in the gap between the keeper and short third

Rasikh Salam to Samson, SIX, he's picked the bones out of that has Sanju Samson. Slower full delivery bowled right in the arc outside off, Samson clears his front leg and clubs it for a mighty maximum over long-on

Kuldeep Yadav to Shubham Dubey, no run, slower and fuller on leg stump, Dubey misses the flick and gets knocked on the front pad. Half-hearted appeal from Pant, but Kuldeep Yadav wasn't genuinely interested in that
Kuldeep Yadav to Samson, 1 run, full and just outside off, forward and driven down to long-off
Kuldeep Yadav to Shubham Dubey, 1 run, driven to the left of the bowler, a slight misfield enables a quick single
Kuldeep Yadav to Samson, 1 run, eased down to long-off

Kuldeep Yadav to Samson, SIX, smoked into the stands. FIFTY UP for the RR skipper. Tossed up on and around off, Samson clears his front leg and packs it into the long-on orbit with plenty of bottom hand power

Kuldeep Yadav to Samson, no ball, Kuldeep Yadav disturbs the stumps in his followthrough and hence it has been called a no-ball. Freehit coming up. Samson flicks this to the right of mid-wicket and decides against a quick single
Kuldeep Yadav to Samson, no run, short outside off, forced towards mid-off
Kuldeep Yadav [2.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Shubham Dubey, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Rasikh Salam to Riyan Parag, out Bowled!! Just moments ago, Ricky Ponting - on the sidelines interview - mentioned that they were tempted to bring in a batter for impact sub, but went with Rasikh Salam becuase of the variety he offers with the ball. Gee, this young boy has repaid the faith of his coach. What a timely, crucial wicket this for the hosts. Back-of-the-hand slower delivery that hits the top of off. So gently that Parag had to turn back and check if the bail had actually fallen off. Rasikh Salam bowled it on a length and managed to get it well under the pull attempt of Parag. Riyan Parag b Rasikh Salam 27(22) [4s-1 6s-3]
Rasikh Salam to Riyan Parag, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!
Rasikh Salam to Riyan Parag, wide, low full toss dished well wide of off as Parag shoulders arms
Rasikh Salam to Samson, 1 run, full and wide of off at I0$, Samson toe-ends the drive to long-off
Rasikh Salam to Riyan Parag, 1 run, back of a length on and around off, knocked away to wide long-on for an easy single
Rasikh Salam to Riyan Parag, SIX, absolute nonchalance from Riyan Parag. Picks the length early, sits on the back foot and smokes the pull for an 89-metre maximum over mid-wicket
Rasikh Salam to Riyan Parag, no run, gets extra bounce on this wobble-seam length delivery outside off, Parag looks to cut it square and gets beaten on the outside edge
Rasikh Salam to Samson, 1 run, I0$ length delivery on the stumps, Samson hangs inside the crease and punches it down to long-on
Rasikh Dar Salam, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Here comes the impact sub...
Axar to Riyan Parag, no run, slider on the stumps, Parag pushes it back to the bowler
Axar to Samson, 1 run, flatter on off-stump, punched firmly to the left of long-off
Axar to Riyan Parag, 1 run, nudged away into the mid-wicket pocket
Axar to Riyan Parag, FOUR, Parag goes for the reverse sweep-slap and executes it perfectly. Got into the position early and timed the ball in the gap between backward point and short third
Axar to Riyan Parag, no run, short and just outside off, Parag chips the drive to the right of cover
Axar to Samson, 1 run, quicker and closer to off, Samson forces the drive to cover and hurries across for a quick single

Kuldeep Yadav to Riyan Parag, SIX, floaty full delivery outside off, Parag sinks to one knee and carves it over deep cover for a mighty maximum. Too much air and Parag got under it nicely to get the desired result...
Kuldeep Yadav to Samson, 1 run, loopy on leg stump, Samson drills it down to long-on
Kuldeep Yadav to Riyan Parag, 1 run, quicker outside off, Parag opens the bat face and steers it square on the off-side
Kuldeep Yadav to Riyan Parag, no run, make that two in a row from Riyan Parag. Kuldeep Yadav did well to shorten the length on this occasion...
Kuldeep Yadav to Riyan Parag, no run, slower and spinning away outside off, Parag expects it to twirl past the wide tramline and shoulders arms. Not to be. It was well inside the guide line...
Kuldeep Yadav to Riyan Parag, no run, quicker outside off, Parag punches it off the back foot into the covers
The required rate is exactly 12 now

Axar to Riyan Parag, 1 run, a direct hit would have been interesting, not to be. Parag gets a leading edge on the flick towards mid-off and looks to pinch a quick single, the fielder tried his best but needed a direct hit to catch Parag short of his crease
Axar to Riyan Parag, no run, short outside off, Parag cuts it to the right of cover

Axar to Riyan Parag, SIX, in the air and over the ropes! Axar slows it up and bowls it full outside off, Parag mistimes the loft off the cue end but that's got enough power to carry all the way over long-off
Axar to Riyan Parag, no run, hint of width outside off, Parag cuts but can't get it past the fielder at backward point
Axar to Riyan Parag, no run, full and straight, driven back to the bowler
Axar to Samson, 1 run, fuller on off, driven firmly down to long-off
Kuldeep Yadav to Riyan Parag, no run, on a length outside off, Riyan Parag rocks back and carves it towards short third. Slip had moved out before this delivery. Tidy start from Kuldeep Yadav
Kuldeep Yadav to Riyan Parag, no run, 91.2kph back of a length ball outside off, the slider perhaps, Riyan Parag looks to cut it through backward point but chops it towards first slip
Kuldeep Yadav to Samson, 1 run, fired in on a back of a length at 112.9kph on middle, Samson plays it uppishly and it goes on the bounce to deep mid-wicket
Kuldeep Yadav to Riyan Parag, 1 run, floated full ball outside off, Riyan Parag square drives it to deep point
A slip in place for Riyan Parag
Kuldeep Yadav to Samson, 1 run, tossed up full ball outside off, Samson strokes it down to long-off

Kuldeep Yadav to Samson, no run, turn straightaway! On a back of a length on off and it's the googly, Samson didn't read it as he got into a tangle. Pushes at it tamely and got beaten on the outside edge
Kuldeep Yadav, comes into the attack

Time for the strategic break! Jaiswal was nipped out early by Khaleel. Samson came in and has looked fluent from the word-go. Buttler was being tied down by some smart bowling from the DC pacers. It was to the spin of Axar that he succumbed to on the penultimate ball of the powerplay. The game is in the balance at present. Overs of Axar and Kuldeep will be crucial for DC

Highlights (Overs 1-6): -- Jaiswal gets out 2nd ball of the innings -- Ishant bowls 4 dots and concedes just 2 off his 1st over -- Khaleel goes for 18 in his 2nd over -- Samson smashes 2 fours and a six off Ishant -- Stubbs drops Buttler on 8 off Mukesh -- Buttler hits Axar for a 4 & 6, but gets bowled off his 5th ball
Axar to Riyan Parag, no run, tossed up generously around off, holds up a bit, Riyan Parag eases it towards extra cover
Riyan Parag, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Axar to Buttler, out Bowled!! The ploy to bowl spin inside the powerplay has worked for DC! A tossed up delivery on a fuller length outside off, Buttler throws his bat at it but only manages to get an inside edge which crashes into the stumps. Buttler's scratchy stay comes to an end. Buttler b Axar 19(17) [4s-2 6s-1]
Axar to Buttler, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!
Axar to Buttler, SIX, in the slot for Buttler. He clears his front leg and smashes it over long-on for a maximum. Hit that one with authority
Axar to Buttler, no run, comes in with the arm again and cramps Buttler for room. He can only chop it to extra cover
Axar to Buttler, no run, coming in with the arm and on a back of a length, cut towards point
Axar to Buttler, FOUR, Buttler joins the party! A tossed up length ball outside off, Buttler picks his spot and hits it over extra cover for a one-bounce boundary
Axar Patel, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack

Mukesh Kumar to Samson, FOUR, the 50-run stand comes up between the duo! A low full-toss around off, Samson shows the full face of the bat and drives it past the left side of mid-on to get the desired result. 15 off the over
Mukesh Kumar to Samson, FOUR, a back of a length ball angling in, Samson stays still and swipes it over square leg for a boundary. He is looking in the zone and looks set for a big one. 50 up for RR

Mukesh Kumar to Samson, SIX, that made a cracking sound off the bat! A back of a length ball around off, Samson stays low in his stance which allows him to get into a position to play the flat-batted stroke. He launches it over long-on and the ball sails over the fence
Mukesh Kumar to Samson, no run, short of length ball outside off, Samson hangs back and knocks it towards mid-off
Mukesh Kumar to Samson, no run, back of a length ball on off, punched towards mid-on

Mukesh Kumar to Buttler, 1 run, dropped! Stubbs didn't quite looked settled there and misses it eventually. A fuller length ball outside off, Buttler looks to slog it across but gets a leading edge towards point. A lot of hang time there. He misjudges it a bit and gets low to catch it reverse cup but the ball pops out. He has a second attempt at it but misses again. How costly will this prove?
Mukesh Kumar, right-arm medium, comes into the attack

Ishant to Samson, SIX, hit with authority! A back of a length ball in the off-stump channel, Samson maintains a good base and smashes it over wide long-on for a maximum. He is motoring along. 15 off the over
Ishant to Samson, FOUR, a full ball shaping towards the pads, easy pickings for Samson as he flicks it uppishly through backward square leg to pick up another boundary
Ishant to Samson, no run, beaten! A back of a length ball outside off, seams in with some extra bounce, Samson tries to run it down past short third but only meets thin air
Third man comes inside the circle. There's a deep backward point in place

Ishant to Samson, FOUR, Samson is timing them like a charm tonight! Another slower shortish ball wide outside off, Samson uses his reach and cuts it through covers to get the desired result once again
Ishant to Buttler, 1 run, a slower full-toss at 115.4kph dipping at Buttler. He is early into his shot and drags it towards deep backward square leg
Ishant to Buttler, no run, Buttler is struggling a bit! A length ball angling in from outside off, Buttler drivess it off the toe-end towards mid-off. Samson comes up and has a chat with Buttler
Khaleel Ahmed to Samson, FOUR, sublime timing! A back of a length ball and a bit of width on offer, Samson stands tall and punches it past extra cover for a rocketing boundary. 18 runs off the over

Khaleel Ahmed to Buttler, 1 run, close shave! An off-cutter on a back of a length outside off, Buttler reaches out to it and drags his shot but hasn't got any sort of momentum behind it. Khaleel Ahmed sticks his left hand out on his followthrough but it just evades him

Khaleel Ahmed to Buttler, FOUR, Khaleel Ahmed switches back to over the wicket to Buttler. It's a length ball shaping away from the batter. He hits it off the toe-end towards mid-on but has got enough on it to beat the dive of the fielder to his left
Khaleel Ahmed to Samson, 1 run, Khaleel Ahmed switches to round the wicket and angles in a back of a length delivery, Samson cuts it to deep backward point

Khaleel Ahmed to Samson, SIX, smashed! A back of a length ball outside off, Samson stays well-balanced and flat-bats it over long-on for a maximum. Held his shape there and used his power to good effect. 200th maximum for Samson in IPL
Khaleel Ahmed to Buttler, 1 run, 139kph full delivery, swings in this time on middle, Buttler stays alert to it and digs it out towards mid-on
Khaleel Ahmed to Buttler, wide, 138.1kph full ball wide outside off, moving further away, Buttler goes after it but only meets thin air. Wided
Ishant to Buttler, 1 run, Buttler walks down the track and Ishant shortens his length outside off. Punched towards cover-point for a brisk single. Brilliant start from Ishant, only 2 off the over
